Title: Protein Bites
Description:

  • 1/3 cup coconut flakes

  • 1/2 cup ground flaxseed

  • 1/2 cup chocolate chips

  • 2 scoop protein powder

  • 1/2 cup peanut butter

  • 1/3 cup honey

  • 1 teaspoon vanilla extract

1. Mix wet ingredients in a large bowl.

Title: Maple Dijon Chicken
Description:
Ingredients:

For the sauce:

  • 1/4 cup low sodium soy sauce (gf or regular)

  • 3 tbsp coconut aminos

  • 3 tbsp Dijon mustard

  • 1 tbsp maple syrup

For the main dish:

  • 1 TBSP Olive oil

  • Salt and Pepper to taste

  • 1 bag (24oz) Baby potatoes

  • 1 bag (12oz) Green beans

  • 20 oz or 5 Chicken thighs (sub chicken breasts if desire)

Directions:

  1. Mix ingredients to make sauce

  2. Pour sauce over chicken in air tight container.

  3. Marinate chicken in fridge for 2-4 hours or overnight

  4. Add potatoes and green beans to pan and cover with olive oil, salt, and pepper.

  5. Add marinated chicken to pan.

  6. Bake for 30 mins at 400 degrees Fahrenheit or until chicken reaches internal temperature of 165 degrees Fahrenheit.

  7. Separate into 4-5 servings and store in fridge.

Title: Butternut Squash Mac
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 butternut squash

  • 1/2 c nutritional yeast

  • 1/4 c bone broth

  • 6 stalks of green onion

  • 1 tsp pepper

  • 1 tsp salt

  • (for non-IBS individuals) 1 head of garlic

  • 150g of gluten free pasta

  • 1 lb. 97% lean ground beef

Directions:

  1. Cut squash in half and roast squash for 45 minutes at 400 degrees F or until mushy. Let cool. (If you plan to add head of garlic, roast in oven with squash).

  2. Scoop out inside contents of squash and add to blender cup.

  3. Add nutrition yeast, broth, chopped green onion, and spices to blender.

  4. Blend until smooth.

  5. Pour over cooked beef and serve over pasta.

For individuals with IBS, butternut squash is not a low FODMAP food however, it is considered to be low FODMAP when consumed in quantities less than approximately 2.65oz and can be tolerated in moderation. Note: garlic is also a high FODMAP food and should not be added if meal preparation is for individuals with IBS.

Please note, individuals with IBS tolerate foods on a case by case basis and should work with a dietitian to determine specific dietary needs.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 4 servings

1 serving: 363 calories, 5 g fat, 44 g carbohydrates, 34 g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Butternut Squash Mac

Title: Candied Cranberries
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 bag of fresh cranberries

  • sparkling lemon or lime beverage of choice

  • 3/4 c coconut sugar

Directions:

  1. Soak cranberries in sparkling beverage for 24 hours.

  2. Drain liquid from cranberries.

  3. Add coconut sugar and shake in container until all berries are coated.

  4. Place coated cranberries on sheet pan and bake for 8 minutes at 200 degrees F.

  5. Remove from oven. Let cool for 5 minutes.

  6. Place in freezer for 15 minutes.

  7. Throw into a serving dish and enjoy!

This recipe is gluten and dairy free and can be made refined sugar free based on beverage selected. For refined sugar free options, choose mineral water and fresh lemon or lime juice!

For a sweeter taste, sub powdered sugar for coconut sugar!

Title: Instant Pot Chili
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 yellow onion, chopped 

  • 3 cloves garlic, finely chopped 

  • 2 Tbsp tomato paste

  • 2 lbs lean ground beef

  • 2 cups beef bone broth

  • 1 (15-oz.) can black beans, rinsed, drained

  • 1 (15-oz.) can fire-roasted diced tomatoes

  • 1 (15-oz.) can kidney beans, rinsed, drained

  • 1 (15-oz.) can black eyed peas, rinsed, drained

  • 1.5 Tbsp chili powder

  • 1 tsp. dried oregano 

  • 1 tsp. ground cumin 

  • 1/2 tsp. cayenne

  • Kosher salt

  • Freshly ground black pepper

Optional Toppings:

  • Shredded cheddar cheese

  • Sour cream or Greek yogurt for a high protein/low fat sub

  • Fritos or corn chips

  • Chopped green onions

(Toppings not included in Cronometer recipe)

Directions:

  1. Sauté: Set Instant Pot to Sauté and cook onion, garlic, and ground beef until browned (5-7 minutes). If using ground beef with higher fat content, you may want to drain the fat. With ~93% lean beef, draining isn't necessary.

  2. Add Ingredients: Return the ground beef mixture to the pot. Add black beans, tomatoes, kidney beans, black-eyed peas, bone broth, spices, salt, and pepper. Lock the lid and Pressure Cook on High for 14 minutes.

  3. Release Pressure: Perform a quick pressure release, then open the lid once fully released.

  4. Serve: Divide chili into bowls and top with your favorite toppings.

    For Slow Cooker: Cook beef in a skillet, then transfer it along with all other ingredients to a slow cooker. Cook on Low for ~6 hours or High for ~3 hours.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 8 servings

1 serving: 430 calories, 11g fat, 38g carbohydrates, 45g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Instant Pot Chili

Title: Meal Prep Breakfast Burritos
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 6 large tortillas (whole wheat or low-carb options for extra fiber)

  • 6 large eggs

  • 1 cup egg whites

  • 1 cup shredded cheese (cheddar, Monterey Jack, Mozzarella, or your favorite variety)

  • 1 lb ground turkey sausage

  • 1/2 tsp salt

  • 1/2 tsp black pepper

  • 1/2 tsp paprika

  • 1/4 tsp garlic powder

  • Cooking spray or 1 tsp olive oil

Directions:

  1. Cook the Turkey Sausage

    • Heat a skillet over medium heat. Spray with cooking spray.

    • Add turkey sausage and cook until browned and fully cooked, about 8–10 minutes.

    • Season with smoked paprika and garlic powder. Set aside.

  2. Prepare the Eggs

    • In a mixing bowl, whisk together eggs and egg whites with salt and pepper.

    • In the same skillet (wipe clean if needed), lightly spray with cooking spray and pour in the egg mixture.

    • Cook on low-medium heat, stirring gently to create soft scrambled eggs. Remove from heat.

    • Combine the eggs, turkey sausage, and cheese in a bowl. Stir to combine.

  3. Assemble the Burritos

    • Lay out each tortilla.

    • Add a portion of the mixture (~3/4-1 cup) to the center of each tortilla.

  4. Wrap the Burritos

    • Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll tightly from bottom to top to form a burrito.

    • Repeat with all tortillas.

    • Optional: Briefly brown the seam-side of each burrito in the skillet to help seal it shut.

  5. Store for Meal Prep

    • Fridge: Wrap each burrito in foil or parchment paper and store in an airtight container. Refrigerate for up to 5 days.

    • Freezer: Wrap burritos individually in plastic wrap, then foil, and place them in a freezer bag. Freeze for up to 3 months.

  6. Reheat Before Eating

    • From the fridge: Microwave for 1–1:30 minutes, flipping halfway.

    • From the freezer: Microwave for 3–4 minutes, flipping halfway.

These burritos are great on their own or dipped in salsa. You can pair them with fresh fruit for a complete breakfast. Need extra calories? Swap egg whites for whole eggs, add more cheese, or mix in veggies like sautéed bell peppers or spinach.

Enjoy your delicious, protein-packed breakfast burritos!

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 6 servings

1 serving: 400 calories, 20g fat, 25g carbohydrates, 33g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Meal Prep Breakfast Burritos

#mealprep #breakfast #protein #easymeal #breakfastburrito #eggs

Title: Chocolate Covered Strawberries
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 pint fresh strawberries, washed and dried thoroughly

  • 6-8 oz dark chocolate melting wafers

  • Optional toppings: crushed nuts, shredded coconut

Other fun add ins: chia seeds, dried cherries, cinnamon, pumpkin, sunflower seeds, raisins, cocoa powder

Directions:

1. Prep: Line a baking sheet with parchment or waxed paper. Place toppings on small plates if using.

  1. Melt Chocolate: Using a double boiler or microwave in 30-second intervals, stirring in between, melt the chocolate until smooth.

  2. Dip: Hold each strawberry by the stem, dip into the melted chocolate, and twist slightly to remove excess. If using toppings, dip immediately before placing on the baking sheet.

  3. Drizzle (Optional): Drizzle leftover chocolate with a fork over the dipped strawberries. Can also opt to use a different chocolate (white or milk) for drizzle.

  4. Set: Chill in the refrigerator for about 15 minutes until the chocolate hardens.

  5. Enjoy! Store in a cool place and enjoy within 24 hours for the best taste.

Title: Mediterranean Chicken Shawarma Bowls
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Chicken:

  • 1 Tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil

  • 1 Tbsp. smoked paprika

  • 2 tsp. ground coriander

  • 1 ½ tsp. kosher salt

  • 1 tsp. ground cumin

  • ½ tsp. ground turmeric

  • ¼ tsp. cayenne pepper

  • ¼ tsp. ground cinnamon

  • Freshly ground black pepper (to taste)

  • 2 lb. boneless, skinless chicken thighs

For the Bowls:

  • 1.5 cup long-grain white rice

  • Kosher salt

  • 2 tsp. extra-virgin olive oil

  • 2 medium cucumbers, sliced into halves

  • 2 bell peppers, chopped

  • ½ red onion, thinly sliced

  • 1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved

  • ½ cup crumbled feta cheese

  • Pinch of crushed red pepper flakes

  • Juice of 1 lemon

  • Store-bought or homemade tzatziki sauce

  • Store-bought or homemade hummus

  • Pita bread

Directions:

  1. Marinate Chicken: In a bowl, mix oil, spices, and salt. Add chicken, toss to coat, and marinate for 30 minutes (or up to 3 hours in the fridge).

  2. Cook Rice: In a pot, bring rice, salt, and 3 cups water to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 15 minutes. Let sit for 10 minutes, then fluff with a fork.

  3. Cook Chicken: Spray the pan with oil and heat over medium-high heat. Cook chicken for 5-7 minutes per side until golden brown and 165°F internally. Let rest for10 minutes, then slice.

  4. Make Salad: In a bowl, combine cucumbers, bell peppers, onion, tomatoes, and feta. Add red pepper flakes, juice from 1 lemon, and 2 tsp. oil. Toss and season with salt.

  5. Assemble Bowls: Divide rice among bowls. Top with chicken, salad, a 1 TBSP of tzatziki sauce, 1 TBSP hummus. Serve with pita.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 5 servings

1 serving: 547 calories, 20g fat, 32g carb, 58g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Mediterranean Chicken Shawarma Bowls

#lunch #recipes #mealprep #highprotein

Title: Slow-Cooker Korean Beef Rice Bowls
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Beef:

  • 1 (2-inch) piece ginger, peeled and finely chopped

  • 4 cloves garlic, finely chopped

  • ¾ cup low-sodium beef broth

  • ½ cup packed light brown sugar

  • ⅓ cup reduced-sodium soy sauce

  • ¼ cup gochujang

  • 2 Tbsp. toasted sesame oil

  • 2 Tbsp. unseasoned rice vinegar

  • 1 Tbsp. cornstarch

  • 3 lb. beef top round, excess fat trimmed, cut into 1 ½-inch pieces

For the main dish:

  • 2 cup white rice

  • Kosher salt

  • Chopped scallions

  • Chopped fresh cilantro

  • Toasted sesame seeds

  • Optional: Roasted broccoli for added fiber and nutrients

Directions:

  1. In a 6-quart slow cooker, whisk together ginger, garlic, broth, brown sugar, soy sauce, gochujang, sesame oil, vinegar, and cornstarch.

  2. Add beef to the slow cooker and mix to coat. Cover and cook on high for 5-6 hours until beef is tender. Turn off slow cooker and let cool for 15 minutes.

  3. Skim excess fat from the surface, then stir the sauce. Shred beef with two forks and mix to combine.

  4. In a pot, bring rice, salt, and 4 cups water to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 15 minutes. Let sit for 10 minutes, then fluff with a fork.

  5. Serve: Spoon beef and sauce over cooked rice. Top with scallions, cilantro, and sesame seeds.

  6. Optional: Serve with steamed or roasted broccoli for added fiber, nutrients, and a well balanced meal

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 8 servings

1 serving: 432 calories, 11g fat, 30g carb, 54g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Slow-Cooker Korean Beef Rice Bowls

#lunch #recipes #mealprep #crockpot #slowcooker #highprotein

Title: Deconstructed Burger Bowls
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Burgers:

  • 1 lb (93% lean) ground beef

  • ½ tsp. onion powder

  • ½ tsp. garlic powder

  • 1 tsp. paprika

  • 1 tsp. salt

  • ½ tsp. black pepper

For the Main Dish:

  • Romaine lettuce

  • Cherry tomates, halved

  • Pickles

  • Red Onion, chopped

For the Sauce:

  • ¼ cup plain non-fat Greek yogurt

  • 1 TBSP ketchup

  • 1 tsp. yellow mustard

  • ½ tsp. garlic powder

  • ½ tsp. onion powder

Directions:

  2. In a bowl, mix the ground beef with the spices until well combined. Then, form the mixture into four equal burger patties.

  3. Cook the patties for about 3-4 minutes per side, or until fully cooked through. Alternatively, you can cook the beef as crumbles by browning it in the skillet, breaking it up as it cooks.

  5. Assemble the burger bowls by layering romaine lettuce as the base, followed by the cooked burger patties (or crumbled beef) and toppings of your choice.

  6. Drizzle the special sauce over everything and enjoy!

Title: Sheet Pan BBQ Chicken with Roasted Veggies
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Chicken:

  • 1 ½ lbs boneless, skinless chicken thighs (or breasts)

  • ½ cup no-sugar-added BBQ sauce

  • 1 tbsp olive oil

  • 1 tsp smoked paprika

  • ½ tsp garlic powder

  • ½ tsp onion powder

  • ½ tsp sea salt

  • ¼ tsp black pepper

For the Veggies:

  • 2 medium sweet potatoes, diced

  • 2 cups broccoli florets

  • 1 red bell pepper, sliced

  • 1 tbsp olive oil

  • ½ tsp sea salt

  • ½ tsp garlic powder

  • ¼ tsp black pepper

Garnishes (Optional)

  • Fresh parsley or green onions

  • Extra BBQ sauce for serving

  • Lemon wedge

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C) and line a sheet pan with parchment paper.

  2. Mix BBQ sauce, olive oil, and seasonings in a bowl. Coat the chicken and set aside.

  3. Toss sweet potatoes with olive oil, salt, and garlic powder. Spread on the sheet pan and roast for 15 minutes.

  4. Remove the pan, place the chicken in the center, and add broccoli and bell pepper tossed with olive oil, salt, and pepper.

  5. Roast Everything Together for 20-25 minutes until the chicken reaches 165°F, sweet potatoes are tender, and veggies are slightly charred.

  6. Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes, then slice.

  7. Drizzle with extra BBQ sauce, garnish, and serve with lemon wedges.

  8. Great for meal prep with a side of quinoa, brown rice, or extra greens!

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 5 servings

1 serving: 363 calories, 12g fat, 17g carb, 44g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Sheet Pan BBQ Chicken with Roasted Veggies

Title: Slow-Roasted Salmon Quinoa Bowl
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Salmon:

  • 1.25lb salmon fillet (5, 4oz fillets)

  • 1 cup pickled cucumbers

For Quick Pickled Cucumbers:

  • 1 English cucumber (or 2 smaller cucumbers), thinly sliced

  • ½ cup rice vinegar (or apple cider vinegar)

  • 1 tsp salt

  • 1 tsp sugar

For the Creamy Dill Yogurt Dressing:

  • 1 cup Greek yogurt

  • ¼ cup fresh dill, chopped (or 2 tsp dried)

  • 1 lemon, juiced

  • 2 garlic cloves, minced

  • 2 tbsp olive oil

  • 2 tbsp water (to thin, if needed)

  • Salt & pepper to taste

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 275°F (135°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

  2. Place salmon fillets on the baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika.

  3. Top salmon with lemon slices and slow roast for 30–35 minutes until tender and flaky.

  4. In a small bowl, mix vinegar, salt, and sugar until dissolved. Add cucumber slices and let sit for at least 15 minutes.

  5. In another bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, dill, lemon juice, garlic, and olive oil. Thin with water if needed and season with salt and pepper.

  6. Divide cooked quinoa or rice into 4-5 bowls. Top with salmon, pickled cucumbers, red onion, and avocado.

  7. Drizzle with creamy dill dressing and garnish with fresh dill or lemon wedges if desired.

Title: Sheet Pan Garlic Shrimp and Roasted Veggies
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb shrimp, peeled and deveined

  • 2 yellow onions, peeled and sliced

  • 2 cups broccoli florets

  • 2 red bell peppers, thinly sliced

  • Lemon (for serving)

  • 1/4 cup avocado oil

  • 2 TBSP minced garlic

  • 1 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes

  • Salt to taste

  • Ground black pepper to taste

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C) and line a sheet pan with parchment paper.

  2. Mix in a medium size bowl avocado oil, garlic, red pepper flakes, parsley, salt and pepper. Toss in shrimp and set aside to marinate.

  3. Toss onions, broccoli, and red peppers with a drizzle or spray of avocado oil and season with salt and pepper. Spread on the sheet pan and roast for 20 minutes.

  4. Remove the pan, pour shrimp and marinade over roasted veggies. Spread out in a single layer and roast for an additional 5 minutes or until shrimp is pink. If shrimp are still slightly frozen roast longer ~10min.

  5. Serve with a lemon wedge.

  6. Great for meal prep with a side of whole wheat pasta, brown rice, quinoa, or greens.

1 serving: 253 calories, 13g fat, 13g carb, 23g protein

Title: Grilled BBQ Chicken Bowls
Description:
Ingredients:

For the BBQ Chicken:

  • 1.5 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts

  • ½ cup BBQ sauce (plus extra for topping)

  • 1 tbsp olive oil

  • 1 tsp garlic powder

  • 1 tsp smoked paprika

  • ½ tsp salt

  • ½ tsp black pepper

For the Coleslaw:

  • 3 cups shredded cabbage (or coleslaw mix)

  • ½ cup plain Greek yogurt

  • 1 tbsp apple cider vinegar

  • 1 tsp Dijon mustard

  • ½ tsp salt

  • ½ tsp black pepper

For the Bowls:

  • 2.5 cups cooked rice (white or brown)

  • ½ cup sliced pickles (or more to taste)

Directions:

  1. In a bowl, mix olive oil, BBQ sauce, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and pepper.

  2. Coat the chicken evenly and let it marinate for at least 15 minutes.

  3. Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Grill the chicken for 6-8 minutes per side until fully cooked (internal temperature of 165°F). Let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.

  4. In a large bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, apple cider vinegar, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper.

  5. Add the shredded cabbage and mix until well coated.

  6. Divide the cooked rice among five containers (1/2 cup per container)

  7. Top each with sliced BBQ chicken, a scoop of coleslaw, and sliced pickles.

  8. Drizzle with extra BBQ sauce if desired.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 5 servings

1 serving: 412 calories, 8g fat, 39g carb, 47g protein

Title: Harissa Roasted Chicken & Sweet Potatoes
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 2 lb. boneless skinless chicken thighs

  • Kosher salt & black pepper

  • 3 Tbsp. harissa

  • Juice of ½ lemon

  • 2 cloves garlic, minced

  • 3 large sweet potatoes, sliced

  • 1 red onion, sliced

  • 2 Tbsp. olive oil

  • 1 tbsp. ground cumin

  • Fresh cilantro & lemon wedges for serving

Directions:

  1. Season chicken with salt & pepper. Mix with harissa, lemon juice, and garlic. Let sit.

  2. Toss sweet potatoes & onion with oil, cumin, salt & pepper. Spread on a baking sheet & bake at 425°F for 10-15 min.

  3. Nestle chicken into the veggies & bake for another 20-25 min until chicken reaches 165°F.

  4. Top with cilantro & serve with lemon wedges.

Title: Lemon Chicken Orzo Salad
Description:
Ingredients:

For the Dressing:

  • 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil

  • 1/2 cup lemon juice + 2 tbsp zest

  • 1 tbsp Dijon mustard

Title: Sheet Pan Chicken Fajitas

Title: Tropical Grill Kabobs
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 1 lb chicken breast, cut into 1.5-inch chunks

  • 1 lb steak (sirloin or flank), cut into 1.5-inch chunks

  • 1 red bell pepper, cut into 1.5-inch pieces

  • 1 yellow bell pepper, cut into 1.5-inch pieces

  • 1 red onion, cut into 1.5-inch wedges

  • 1 ½ cups pineapple chunks (fresh or canned in juice)

  • Wooden skewers (about 10–12)

For the Marinade⅓ cup olive oil

  • ¼ cup soy sauce

  • 2 tbsp honey or maple syrup

  • 2 tbsp lime juice

  • 2 cloves garlic, minced

  • 1 tsp smoked paprika

  • ½ tsp black pepper

  • Optional: ½ tsp red pepper flakes for a kick

Directions:

  1. Soak the wooden skewers in water for at least 30 minutes to prevent burning on the grill.

  2. In a large bowl or zip-top bag, whisk together all marinade ingredients.

  3. Add the chicken, steak, bell peppers, onion, and pineapple to the marinade. Toss to coat evenly. Cover and marinate in the fridge for at least 1 hour, or up to 8 hours for deeper flavor.

  4. Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.

  5. Thread the marinated ingredients onto the soaked skewers, alternating between chicken, steak, veggies, and pineapple for a colorful presentation.

  6. Grill the kabobs for 10–15 minutes, turning every few minutes, until the chicken is fully cooked (165°F internal temp) and the steak reaches desired doneness.

  7. Remove from grill and let rest for a few minutes before serving.

  8. Serve over rice, quinoa, or with a side salad for a fresh summer meal. These kabobs are great for meal prep or BBQ gatherings!

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: about 12 kabobs

1 kabob (125g): 153 calories, 5g fat, 7g carb, 21g protein

Title: Hashbrown Egg Casserole with Feta, Spinach & Sundried Tomatoes
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 12 large eggs

  • 3 cups frozen hashbrowns, thawed

  • 1 block feta cheese, cubed

  • 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped

  • ½ cup sundried tomatoes, chopped (drained if oil-packed)

  • 1 small onion, diced

  • Salt and pepper, to taste

  • Olive oil or cooking spray, for greasing

Directions:

  1. Preheat oven to 425°F.

  2. Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish (or use two smaller ones if needed).

  3. spread the thawed hash brown in the bottom. If still frozen bake for ~5-10 minutes.

  4. In a large mixing bowl, whisk the 12 eggs thoroughly. Add salt, pepper, and any optional seasonings.

  5. Pour over hashbrowns.

  6. Top with feta, spinach, sundried tomatoes, and diced onion.

  7. Bake for 20-30 minutes, or until the eggs are set.

  8. Let cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.

Title: Slow Cooker Pork Carnitas
Description:
Ingredients:

  • 2 pounds pork tenderloin or pork loin

  • 1 tablespoon dried oregano

  • 2 teaspoons ground cumin

  • 1 tablespoon avocado oil

  • ½ onion, chopped

  • 3 garlic cloves, smashed

  • 1 medium jalapeño, sliced (remove seeds for less heat)

  • 2 teaspoons salt

  • 2 tablespoons fresh lime juice

  • ¼ cup orange juice

Directions:

  1. Assemble in slow cooker: Place the pork loin in the slow cooker. Add oregano, cumin, avocado oil, onion, garlic, jalapeño, salt, lime juice, and orange juice.

  2. Mix: Use tongs or clean hands to gently mix everything together, making sure the pork is coated evenly with the seasonings and juices.

  3. Cook: Cover and cook on HIGH for 4–6 hours or LOW for 6–8 hours, until pork is very tender and reaches an internal temp of 195°F.

  4. Shred: Shred the pork directly in the slow cooker using two forks. Stir to mix with the juices.

  5. Serve or store: Serve immediately, or let cool and store pork with juices in an airtight container in the fridge until ready to eat.

Nutrition Data:

Recipe Yield: 6 servings

1 serving (198g): 205 calories, 6g fat, 4g carb, 32g protein

Cronometer Recipe Name: Fitomics Slow Cooker Pork Carnitas
